Council, (b) Lancashire County Council and (c) the Environment Agency relating to the council district area of Lancaster City Council (i) between December 2015 and March 2016, (ii) between April 2016 and July 2016, (iii) between August 2016 and November 2016 and (iv) in December 2016.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","57535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657867","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-19","<p>In Lancashire, a total of £91.9 million has been allocated to flood and coastal risk management schemes in the Government’s six year capital investment programme between 2016 and 2021.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657867/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-19T12:28:58.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657867/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657867/answer","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657867/answer/previousversion/27030","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-13","Flood Control: Lancaster","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much funding has been allocated to Lancashire for flood defences since December 2015.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","57536"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657868","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-15","<p>We are supporting the horticulture sector to work towards targets for the removal of peat use in horticulture by 2020 for the retail sector and 2030 for the commercial sector as set out in the Natural Environment White Paper published in 2011. Part of this work is focussed on working with the industry on the development of a tool for assessing responsibly sourced and manufactured growing media ingredients.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657868/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-15T11:54:48.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657868/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657868/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-13","Soil","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps her Department is taking to promote the use of more sustainable materials in topsoil and mulch products.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","57523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657869","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-16","<p>Defra does not forecast estimates of the proportion of household waste that will be recycled or the rate of recovery from non-hazardous construction and demolition waste in the UK in future years.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657869/answer",,,,,"57437","2016-12-16T11:18:33.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657869/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657869/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-13","Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of household waste she estimates will be recycled in each of the next three years.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","57434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657870","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-19","<p>The Government last measured soil carbon under the Countryside Survey, carried out in 2007.</p><p> </p><p>It is usual practice for farmers to take their own soil samples and an increasing number of them are having their samples measured to gain a better understanding of their soils and how to manage them.</p><p> </p><p>We have been exploring via a Natural Environment Research Council (NERC) fellowship whether we can use farmer collected data to understand what is happening at a national level.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657870/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-19T08:12:05.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657870/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657870/answer","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657870/answer/previousversion/27029","Biography information for George Eustice","13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-13","Soil: Carbon","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she is taking to collect soil organic carbon level data on farms.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","57435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657871","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-16","<p>Defra does not forecast estimates of the proportion of household waste that will be recycled or the rate of recovery from non-hazardous construction and demolition waste in the UK in future years.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657871/answer",,,,,"57434","2016-12-16T11:18:33.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657871/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657871/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-13","Construction: Waste","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what estimate she has made of the UK rate of recovery from non-hazardous construction and demolition waste for each of the next three years.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","57437"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657872","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-20","<p>The welfare of animals in sanctuaries is provided for under the Animal Welfare Act 2006 which makes it an offence to cause unnecessary suffering to an animal or to fail to provide for an animal’s welfare needs. The Government supports moves by the sector to apply minimum standards in addition to the code of practice for the operation of animal sanctuaries and rehoming centres which the Association of Dogs and Cats Homes has developed. The Government does not currently have plans to make animal sanctuaries subject to specific regulations.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657872/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-20T11:35:50.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657872/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657872/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-13","Animal Welfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent assessment she has made of animal welfare standards in animal sanctuaries; what plans she has to provide for regulatory oversight of animal sanctuaries; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","57474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657873","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-19","<p>Defra does not hold information in relation to the estimated number of birds killed annually by the operation of wind turbines in the UK.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657873/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-19T11:05:52.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657873/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657873/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-13","Wind Power: Birds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what information her Department holds on the estimated number of birds killed annually by the operation of wind turbines.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","57471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657874","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-20","<p>The Government is currently reviewing the laws on the selling of pet animals. Issues relating to the definition of a business constitute part of those considerations.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657874/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-20T11:32:46.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657874/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657874/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-13","Cats: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will develop a clear definition of commercial pet sales to protect the welfare of cats and kittens.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","57410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657875","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-16","<p>The Government does not keep data on water mills.</p><p>The majority of hydro capacity in Great Britain was installed in Scotland in the first hydro revolution in the 1950s, with a smaller amount installed in Wales. The majority of these installations are still operating. In 2015, it was estimated that there were 1,065 operational plants with a capacity of 1,750 Megawatts, generating 6 Terawatt hours (equivalent to 1.8% of UK electricity supply)[1].</p><p>The Government does not monitor the condition of existing hydro power plants in the UK. It is a business decision for companies to determine when to carry out repairs and refurbishments.</p><p> </p><p>[1] www.gov.uk/government/statistics/regional-renewable-statistics</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657875/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-16T13:03:49.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657875/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657875/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-12-13","Water Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many water mills there are in the UK in (a) total, (b) fully working condition, (c) need of repair and (d) need of full rebuilding.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","57332"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657876","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-16","<p>We are currently reviewing the laws on the selling of pet animals with the aim of replacing the Pet Animals Act 1951 with regulations made under the Animal Welfare Act 2006. The purpose of the new regulations will be to ensure that it is easier for local authorities to enforce and to improve animal welfare.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657876/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-16T11:08:56.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657876/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657876/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-13","Pet Animals Act 1951: Enforcement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps her Department takes to monitor the enforcement of the Pet Animals Act 1951 by local authorities.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","57318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657877","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-16","<p>No specific discussions have occurred at Ministerial level on the use of water mills to generate electricity. However officials from the Department of Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS), the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs (DEFRA) and the Environment Agency cooperate closely to ensure that small-scale hydropower is exploited in a sustainable way so as to minimise environmental and other impacts.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657877/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-16T11:11:59.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657877/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657877/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-13","Water Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy on the use of water mills to generate electricity.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","57330"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657878","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-16","<p>The note of the meeting is that to which I referred in my previous response.</p><p> </p><p>The Sheep Dip Sufferers Support Group was provided with the note taken, which they then published on their web site. This is still available at:</p><p><a href="http://www.sheepdipsufferers.uk/campaigning/Summary%20of%20meeting.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.sheepdipsufferers.uk/campaigning/Summary%20of%20meeting.pdf</a></p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657878/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-16T11:16:24.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657878/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657878/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-13","Sheep Dipping: Health Hazards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 8 December 2016 to Question 55615, if she will provide to the Sheep Dip Sufferers Support Group the minutes of the meeting the Minister of State for Agriculture, Fisheries and Food held with it on 19 November 2015.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","57300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657879","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-12-16","<p>The UK welcomes the successful conduct of the elections in The Gambia on 1 December, and congratulates the Gambian people on the orderly and legitimate expression of their desire for change. As the Minister responsible for Africa, I spoke directly to the President-elect, Mr Adama Barrow, last week, to congratulate him on his victory and to offer the UK's support. But we are deeply concerned by President Jammeh's recent rejection of the elections' clear and legitimate result and strongly condemn any attempt to disrupt the peaceful, constitutional transfer of power. We welcome the clear, unified statement of the UN Security Council on 10 December calling for the results to be respected, as well as the efforts of the Economic Community Of West African States to impress on President Jammeh the need to respect the will of the people and ensure a peaceful handover of power to President-elect Barrow.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657879/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-16T14:57:36.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657879/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657879/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-13","Gambia: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has contacted (a) President Yahya Jammeh and (b) his counterpart in the government of the Gambia since the recent general election in that country.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","57361"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657880","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-12-16","<p>The British High Commission in Yaoundé is following the situation closely and has called for restraint and encouraged dialogue. The High Commissioner chaired a meeting with the US, French, Canadians and the EU on 1 December to discuss this matter. The UK supports the independent investigation by the National Commission for Human Rights and Freedoms into the violence and deaths in Bamenda. The UK believes that all parties have a responsibility to uphold and protect the peace and stability of Cameroon and that legal and peaceful means should be used to voice any grievances. The violence has abated and we hope for a swift and peaceful resolution of this matter.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657880/answer",,,,,,"2016-12-16T14:41:35.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657880/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657880/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-13","Cameroon: Demonstrations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his counterpart in the government of Cameroon on finding a peaceful and satisfactory solution to end protests by teachers and lawyers in the north-west and south-west English-speaking regions of Cameroon.","false","Biography information for Rob Marris","Wolverhampton South West","Rob Marris","57362"
